ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This was a wonderful course, I learned a lot about Cleopatra and was able to focus on independent research as well. My classmates and Professor Kleiner were interested in what I had to say and we all created a warm, curious learning environment.

Definitely recommend it to someone who wants to learn more about the period at the time of the fall of Egypt and transition from Hellenism to Augustan Rome, particularly through the eyes of one of the cast of characters.
Yes, I would absolutely recommend to anyone.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I was able to study a sub-discipline that I found important and gained valuable bibliographicalinformation.

My focus is Ancient Greece and Rome. I was very pleased to incorporate some study of Egypt in the first century B. C. in order to provide more context to my studies of the material remains and history of the period.
